article.description: Kelsey Bolte scored 19 points, Lauren Mansfield had 14 points and six rebounds, and No. 25 Iowa State beat Kansas State 58-51 Saturday night.
article.headline: No. 24 Iowa State pulls away from Kansas State after halftime
article.linkText: Iowa St. pulls away from Kansas St. in 2nd half
article.story:
MANHATTAN, Kan. --  Kelsey Bolte scored 19 points, Lauren Mansfield had 14 points and six rebounds, and Iowa State (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) beat Kansas State 58-51 Saturday night.

The Cyclones (20-8, 8-6 Big 12) used a tiebreaking 15-4 run to take a 47-36 lead with about 7 minutes to go and pull away for good.

Jalana Childs had 18 points, Taelor Karr scored 12, and Brittany Chambers added 10 for Kansas State (18-9, 8-6)

Iowa State finished with 34-28 rebounding advantage and made it difficult for the Wildcats (18-9, 8-6) to score the ball inside, Kansas State shot 36 percent from the field, including 3 for 16 on 3-pointers.

The Wildcats stayed within a few points of the Cyclones throughout the first half and part of the second half. The game was tied 32-32 with 13:23 left.
